@startuml
title UC05 - View Registration Period List - Display Registration Periods

hide footbox

actor PrimaryActor as "Admin / Staff"
participant Screen as "Screen"
participant APIClient as "API Client (Frontend)"
participant RegPeriodRouter as "RegistrationPeriodRouter"
participant AuthMiddleware as "AuthMiddleware"
participant RBACMiddleware as "RBACMiddleware"
participant RegPeriodController as "RegistrationPeriodController"
participant RegPeriodService as "RegistrationPeriodService"
participant RegPeriodModel as "RegistrationPeriodModel"
participant UserModel as "UserModel"
database DB as "Database"

activate PrimaryActor
PrimaryActor -> Screen: (1) navigate to Registration Period page
activate Screen

Screen -> APIClient: (2) GET /api/registration-periods
activate APIClient
APIClient -> RegPeriodRouter: (3) forward GET request
activate RegPeriodRouter

RegPeriodRouter -> AuthMiddleware: (4) verify access token
activate AuthMiddleware
AuthMiddleware --> RegPeriodRouter: (4.1) token valid, user authenticated
deactivate AuthMiddleware

RegPeriodRouter -> RBACMiddleware: (5) check permission
activate RBACMiddleware
RBACMiddleware --> RegPeriodRouter: (5.1) permission granted
deactivate RBACMiddleware

RegPeriodRouter -> RegPeriodController: (6) getRegistrationPeriods()
activate RegPeriodController
RegPeriodController -> RegPeriodService: (7) getAllPeriods()
activate RegPeriodService

RegPeriodService -> RegPeriodModel: (8) find().sort({ startDate: -1 })
activate RegPeriodModel
RegPeriodModel -> DB: (9) db query with sort
activate DB
DB --> RegPeriodModel: (10) return period documents
deactivate DB
RegPeriodModel --> RegPeriodService: (11) return periods array
deactivate RegPeriodModel

RegPeriodService -> RegPeriodService: (11.1) auto-update status based on dates
note right
  For each period:
  - If now < startDate → status = 'upcoming'
  - If startDate <= now <= endDate → status = 'active'
  - If now > endDate → status = 'closed'
end note

RegPeriodService -> UserModel: (11.2) populate createdBy field
activate UserModel
UserModel -> DB: (11.3) get creator info
activate DB
DB --> UserModel: (11.4) return users
deactivate DB
UserModel --> RegPeriodService: (11.5) creator names populated
deactivate UserModel

RegPeriodService -> RegPeriodService: (12) format response
RegPeriodService --> RegPeriodController: (13) return { periods, count }
deactivate RegPeriodService

RegPeriodController --> RegPeriodRouter: (14) 200 OK with data
deactivate RegPeriodController
RegPeriodRouter --> APIClient: (15) 200 OK JSON response
deactivate RegPeriodRouter
APIClient --> Screen: (16) render period list
activate Screen
Screen -> Screen: (16.1) highlight active periods
Screen -> Screen: (16.2) format dates display
Screen --> PrimaryActor: (17) display periods with status
deactivate Screen
deactivate APIClient
deactivate PrimaryActor

@enduml
